  "root_text": {
    "dhp179:0.1": "Khuddakanikāya ",
    "dhp179:0.2": "Dhammapada ",
    "dhp179:0.3": "Buddhavagga ",
    "dhp179:0.4": "Māradhītaravatthu ",
    "dhp179:1": "Yassa jitaṁ nāvajīyati, ",
    "dhp179:2": "Jitaṁ yassa noyāti koci loke; ",
    "dhp179:3": "Taṁ buddhamanantagocaraṁ, ",
    "dhp179:4": "Apadaṁ kena padena nessatha. ",
    "dhp180:1": "Yassa jālinī visattikā, ",
    "dhp180:2": "Taṇhā natthi kuhiñci netave; ",
    "dhp180:3": "Taṁ buddhamanantagocaraṁ, ",
    "dhp180:4": "Apadaṁ kena padena nessatha. ",
    "dhp181:0": "Devorohaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp181:1": "Ye jhānapasutā dhīrā, ",
    "dhp181:2": "nekkhammūpasame ratā; ",
    "dhp181:3": "Devāpi tesaṁ pihayanti, ",
    "dhp181:4": "sambuddhānaṁ satīmataṁ. ",
    "dhp182:0": "Erakapattanāgarājavatthu ",
    "dhp182:1": "Kiccho manussapaṭilābho, ",
    "dhp182:2": "kicchaṁ maccāna jīvitaṁ; ",
    "dhp182:3": "Kicchaṁ saddhammassavanaṁ, ",
    "dhp182:4": "kiccho buddhānamuppādo. ",
    "dhp183:0": "Ānandattherapañhavatthu ",
    "dhp183:1": "Sabbapāpassa akaraṇaṁ, ",
    "dhp183:2": "kusalassa upasampadā; ",
    "dhp183:3": "Sacittapariyodapanaṁ, ",
    "dhp183:4": "etaṁ buddhāna sāsanaṁ. ",
    "dhp184:1": "Khantī paramaṁ tapo titikkhā, ",
    "dhp184:2": "Nibbānaṁ paramaṁ vadanti buddhā; ",
    "dhp184:3": "Na hi pabbajito parūpaghātī, ",
    "dhp184:4": "Na samaṇo hoti paraṁ viheṭhayanto. ",
    "dhp185:1": "Anūpavādo anūpaghāto, ",
    "dhp185:2": "Pātimokkhe ca saṁvaro; ",
    "dhp185:3": "Mattaññutā ca bhattasmiṁ, ",
    "dhp185:4": "Pantañca sayanāsanaṁ; ",
    "dhp185:5": "Adhicitte ca āyogo, ",
    "dhp185:6": "Etaṁ buddhāna sāsanaṁ. ",
    "dhp186:0": "Anabhiratabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp186:1": "Na kahāpaṇavassena, ",
    "dhp186:2": "titti kāmesu vijjati; ",
    "dhp186:3": "Appassādā dukhā kāmā, ",
    "dhp186:4": "iti viññāya paṇḍito. ",
    "dhp187:1": "Api dibbesu kāmesu, ",
    "dhp187:2": "ratiṁ so nādhigacchati; ",
    "dhp187:3": "Taṇhakkhayarato hoti, ",
    "dhp187:4": "sammāsambuddhasāvako. ",
    "dhp188:0": "Aggidattabrāhmaṇavatthu ",
    "dhp188:1": "Bahuṁ ve saraṇaṁ yanti, ",
    "dhp188:2": "pabbatāni vanāni ca; ",
    "dhp188:3": "Ārāmarukkhacetyāni, ",
    "dhp188:4": "manussā bhayatajjitā. ",
    "dhp189:1": "Netaṁ kho saraṇaṁ khemaṁ, ",
    "dhp189:2": "netaṁ saraṇamuttamaṁ; ",
    "dhp189:3": "Netaṁ saraṇamāgamma, ",
    "dhp189:4": "sabbadukkhā pamuccati. ",
    "dhp190:1": "Yo ca buddhañca dhammañca, ",
    "dhp190:2": "saṅghañca saraṇaṁ gato; ",
    "dhp190:3": "Cattāri ariyasaccāni, ",
    "dhp190:4": "sammappaññāya passati. ",
    "dhp191:1": "Dukkhaṁ dukkhasamuppādaṁ, ",
    "dhp191:2": "dukkhassa ca atikkamaṁ; ",
    "dhp191:3": "Ariyaṁ caṭṭhaṅgikaṁ maggaṁ, ",
    "dhp191:4": "dukkhūpasamagāminaṁ. ",
    "dhp192:1": "Etaṁ kho saraṇaṁ khemaṁ, ",
    "dhp192:2": "etaṁ saraṇamuttamaṁ; ",
    "dhp192:3": "Etaṁ saraṇamāgamma, ",
    "dhp192:4": "sabbadukkhā pamuccati. ",
    "dhp193:0": "Ānandattherapañhavatthu ",
    "dhp193:1": "Dullabho purisājañño, ",
    "dhp193:2": "na so sabbattha jāyati; ",
    "dhp193:3": "Yattha so jāyati dhīro, ",
    "dhp193:4": "taṁ kulaṁ sukhamedhati. ",
    "dhp194:0": "Sambahulabhikkhuvatthu ",
    "dhp194:1": "Sukho buddhānamuppādo, ",
    "dhp194:2": "sukhā saddhammadesanā; ",
    "dhp194:3": "Sukhā saṅghassa sāmaggī, ",
    "dhp194:4": "samaggānaṁ tapo sukho. ",
    "dhp195:0": "Kassapadasabalassasuvaṇṇacetiyavatthu ",
    "dhp195:1": "Pūjārahe pūjayato, ",
    "dhp195:2": "buddhe yadi va sāvake; ",
    "dhp195:3": "Papañcasamatikkante, ",
    "dhp195:4": "tiṇṇasokapariddave. ",
    "dhp196:1": "Te tādise pūjayato, ",
    "dhp196:2": "nibbute akutobhaye; ",
    "dhp196:3": "Na sakkā puññaṁ saṅkhātuṁ, ",
    "dhp196:4": "imettamapi kenaci. ",
    "dhp196:5": "Buddhavaggo cuddasamo. ",
    "dhp196:6": "Paṭhamabhāṇavāraṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "dhp179:0.1": "Minor Collection ",
    "dhp179:0.2": "Sayings of the Dhamma 179–196 ",
    "dhp179:0.3": "14. The Buddhas ",
    "dhp179:1": "He whose victory may not be undone, ",
    "dhp179:2": "a victory unrivaled in all the world; ",
    "dhp179:3": "by what track would you trace that Buddha, ",
    "dhp179:4": "who leaves no track in his infinite range? ",
    "dhp180:1": "Of craving, the weaver, the clinger, he has none: ",
    "dhp180:2": "so where can he be traced? ",
    "dhp180:3": "By what track would you trace that Buddha, ",
    "dhp180:4": "who leaves no track in his infinite range? ",
    "dhp181:1": "The attentive intent on absorption, ",
    "dhp181:2": "who love the peace of renunciation, ",
    "dhp181:3": "the Buddhas, ever mindful, ",
    "dhp181:4": "are envied by even the gods. ",
    "dhp182:1": "It’s hard to gain a human birth; ",
    "dhp182:2": "the life of mortals is hard; ",
    "dhp182:3": "it’s hard to hear the true teaching; ",
    "dhp182:4": "the arising of Buddhas is hard. ",
    "dhp183:1": "Not to do any evil; ",
    "dhp183:2": "to embrace the good; ",
    "dhp183:3": "to purify one’s mind: ",
    "dhp183:4": "this is the instruction of the Buddhas. ",
    "dhp184:1": "Patient acceptance is the ultimate fervor. ",
    "dhp184:2": "Extinguishment is the ultimate, say the Buddhas. ",
    "dhp184:3": "No true renunciate injures another, ",
    "dhp184:4": "nor does an ascetic hurt another. ",
    "dhp185:1": "Not speaking ill nor doing harm; ",
    "dhp185:2": "restraint in the monastic code; ",
    "dhp185:3": "moderation in eating; ",
    "dhp185:4": "staying in remote lodgings; ",
    "dhp185:5": "commitment to the higher mind—",
    "dhp185:6": "this is the instruction of the Buddhas. ",
    "dhp186:1": "Even if it were raining money, ",
    "dhp186:2": "you’d not be sated in sensual pleasures. ",
    "dhp186:3": "An astute person understands that sensual pleasures ",
    "dhp186:4": "offer little gratification and much suffering. ",
    "dhp187:1": "Thus they find no delight ",
    "dhp187:2": "even in celestial pleasures. ",
    "dhp187:3": "A disciple of the fully awakened Buddha ",
    "dhp187:4": "delights in the ending of craving. ",
    "dhp188:1": "So many go for refuge ",
    "dhp188:2": "to mountains and forest groves, ",
    "dhp188:3": "to shrines in tended parks; ",
    "dhp188:4": "those people are driven by fear. ",
    "dhp189:1": "But such refuge is no sanctuary, ",
    "dhp189:2": "it is no supreme refuge. ",
    "dhp189:3": "By going to that refuge, ",
    "dhp189:4": "you’re not released from all suffering. ",
    "dhp190:1": "One gone for refuge to the Buddha, ",
    "dhp190:2": "to his teaching and to the Saṅgha, ",
    "dhp190:3": "sees the four noble truths ",
    "dhp190:4": "with right understanding: ",
    "dhp191:1": "suffering, suffering’s origin, ",
    "dhp191:2": "suffering’s transcendence, ",
    "dhp191:3": "and the noble eightfold path ",
    "dhp191:4": "that leads to the stilling of suffering. ",
    "dhp192:1": "Such refuge is a sanctuary, ",
    "dhp192:2": "it is the supreme refuge. ",
    "dhp192:3": "By going to that refuge, ",
    "dhp192:4": "you’re released from all suffering. ",
    "dhp193:1": "It’s hard to find a thoroughbred man: ",
    "dhp193:2": "they’re not born just anywhere. ",
    "dhp193:3": "A family where that attentive one is born ",
    "dhp193:4": "prospers in happiness. ",
    "dhp194:1": "Happy, the arising of Buddhas! ",
    "dhp194:2": "Happy, the teaching of Dhamma! ",
    "dhp194:3": "Happy is the harmony of the Saṅgha, ",
    "dhp194:4": "and the striving of the harmonious is happy. ",
    "dhp195:1": "When a person venerates the worthy—",
    "dhp195:2": "the Buddha or his disciple, ",
    "dhp195:3": "who have transcended proliferation, ",
    "dhp195:4": "and have left behind grief and lamentation, ",
    "dhp196:1": "quenched, fearing nothing from any quarter—",
    "dhp196:2": "the merit of one venerating such as these, ",
    "dhp196:3": "cannot be calculated by anyone, ",
    "dhp196:4": "saying it is just this much. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "dhp179:2": "Jitaṁ yassa → jitamassa (bj, sya-all); jitaṁ assa (pts1ed, pts2ed); jitaṁ massa (mr) ",
    "dhp183:2": "kusalassa upasampadā → kusalassūpasampadā (sya-all) ",
    "dhp183:3": "Sacittapariyodapanaṁ → sacittapariyodāpanaṁ (?) ",
    "dhp184:2": "Nibbānaṁ → nibbāṇaṁ (bj) ",
    "dhp184:3": "Na → ayaṁ nakāro bj, sya-all, pts1ed, pts2ed potthakesu na ",
    "dhp185:1": "Anūpavādo anūpaghāto → anupavādo anupaghāto (cck, pts2ed, mr) "
  },
